{"comments":"Exponential and logarithmic functions.\n\nNo JavaScript. No FFI. Pure functional implementations using:\n- Taylor series for exp\n- Arctanh series for log\n- Range reduction for numerical stability\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"Exponential function e^x using Taylor series\n\ne^x = 1 + x + x²/2! + x³/3! + x⁴/4! + ...\n\nFor large |x|, we use range reduction: e^x = e^(x/2) * e^(x/2)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[39,24],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Math/Core/Exponential.purs","start":[39,1]},"title":"exp"},{"children":[],"comments":"exp(x) - 1, more precise for small x\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[72,26],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Math/Core/Exponential.purs","start":[72,1]},"title":"expm1"},{"children":[],"comments":"Natural logarithm using series expansion\n\nFor x near 1, use: ln(x) = 2 * (y + y³/3 + y⁵/5 + ...) where y = (x-1)/(x+1)\nFor other x, use range reduction: ln(x) = ln(x/e^n) + n\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag"